    "created_at": "2017-04-20T09:41:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-20T09:41:19Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We could keep these unknown fields and save them with known fields to preserve them, however when 1 instance knows and changes this field it could be overwritten by 2nd instance with original value. This issue can happen also now with known fields with 2 instances. For different mods it can be solved by settings per mod. Shouldn't we have also settings per parallel install?\r\nOr we don't need to keep these unknown fields after loading them, but rather before saving, load all unknown settings and save new settings file with known fields + unknown fields to prevent overwriting them."
  },
