    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, if you have per mod settings, then they should also be per version. If that is done then another solution would be for mods to look for their latest installed version, copy the settings, and then run an upgrade utility on them. The downside to that is that setting changes won't be carried over to parallel installs or downgrades."
